   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 2868, recto: (1) I, Palou, write to Daniel, saying: I (2) owe you twenty she of bronze.  (3) I am prepared to give them to you without any (4) objection--and they are what I received from you--(5) on the twentieth of Pashons, under (6) Papnoute, the lashane.  I, Palou, (7) assent to this sherd.  I, Abraham, (8) priest of (the Church of) Apa Cyriacus, he requested (9) me and I wrote this sherd with my hand and I (10) witness.</ab>
         </div>
